title: PML-N candidate Babar Hussain wins PP-208 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz candidate Babar Hussain Abid has won the election for Punjab Assembly from PP-208, Khanewal-IV by securing 48,494 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an independent candidate Muhammad Jamsheed Shoukat, who bagged 46288 votes.
The votersâ€™ turn-out remained 53.79 per cent.
